               <p>HENRY HALL. I am an <rs id="t18281204-244-viclabel1292" type="occupation">ironmonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281204-244-victim2124 t18281204-244-viclabel1292"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18281204-244-crimeloc1293">Red Lion-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18281204-244-crimeloc1293" type="placeName" value="Red Lion-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18281204-244-crimeloc1293" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281204-244-off1290 t18281204-244-crimeloc1293"></join>. I lost these rings from my counter on the 3d of December; I saw them safe at a quarter before three o'clock, when the prisoner was there; I saw them afterwards taken from the prisoner's pocket.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281204-244-person2125">
                  MATTHEW 
                  WELDHEN
               <interp inst="t18281204-244-person2125" type="surname" value="WELDHEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-244-person2125" type="given" value="MATTHEW"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-244-person2125" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the street-keeper. The prisoner was given into my custody, and I took these rings from him; he said at first that he did not know any thing about them, but afterwards he said he did it through great distress.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281204-244-person2126">
                  EDWARD 
                  HAUGHTON
               <interp inst="t18281204-244-person2126" type="surname" value="HAUGHTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-244-person2126" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-244-person2126" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am book-keeper to Mr. Hall. The prisoner came in on Wednesday, and asked to look at a lock - while Mr. Hall's back was turned, the prisoner took the rings, and put them into his pocket.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I went to ask the price of a mortice-lock - I saw a label on these rings; I took them up, and put them down again; I never moved from the place.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281204-244-person2127">
